review_text:
@9toast_sg | Singapore’s first honey-glazed toast & sandos.

recently headed down to @9toast_sg for a cute little saturday brunch & thoroughly enjoyed our experience!!

the mentaiko kani shokupan had a rich umami flavor with a generous amount of imitation crab & ebiko for that extra crunch 🦀 the bread was also of the perfect thickness & crunch~

we particularly enjoyed the chicken katsu sando that had a thick crispy fried chicken 🍗 there’s also something about that savoury tangy sauce that complemented the fried chicken so so well 🙂‍↕️

the drinks are also not to be missed!! the purple haze latte had the most generous amount of fresh sweet taro paste — literally orh nee in the form of a drink 🍠 the misu latte was a literal heaven for all the tiramisu lovers out there ☕️ so addictively satisfying!!


@9toast_sg is conveniently located a stone’s throw away from dhoby ghaut mrt & super quiet — perfect conducive study spot ✍🏼💻 do check out their super worth weekday set meal that goes as low as $9.90!!
